      "widgets": [
        {
          "title": "Cluster Health",
          "layout": {
            "column": 1,
            "row": 1,
            "width": 4,
            "height": 1
          },
          "linkedEntityGuids": null,
          "visualization": {
            "id": "viz.markdown"
          },
          "rawConfiguration": {
            "text": "ðŸŸ¢ Green cluster status All primary and replica shards are allocated. Your cluster is 100% healthy and fully operational.\n\nðŸŸ¡ Yellow cluster status At least one replica shard is unallocated or missing. Search results are still complete. You may lose data if more shards disappear.\n\nðŸ”´ Red cluster status At least one primary shard is missing. You are missing data and searches will return partial results. You are unable to index into that shard."
          }
        },
        {
          "title": "Cluster Size",
          "layout": {
            "column": 5,
            "row": 1,
            "width": 4,
            "height": 1
          },
          "linkedEntityGuids": null,
          "visualization": {
            "id": "viz.markdown"
          },
          "rawConfiguration": {
            "text": "Shows the size and scale of your cluster. A sudden drop can indicate that multiple nodes have failed"
          }
        },
        {
          "title": "Pending Tasks",
          "layout": {
            "column": 9,
            "row": 1,
            "width": 4,
            "height": 1
          },
          "linkedEntityGuids": null,
          "visualization": {
            "id": "viz.markdown"
          },
          "rawConfiguration": {
            "text": "A high or continuously growing number of pending tasks indicates the master node is overloaded and can't process cluster changes (like creating indices or updating mappings) quickly enough. This is a key indicator of a performance bottleneck."
          }
        },
        {
          "title": "Cluster Health",
          "layout": {
            "column": 1,
            "row": 2,
            "width": 4,
            "height": 2
          },
          "linkedEntityGuids": [],
          "visualization": {
            "id": "viz.billboard"
          },
          "rawConfiguration": {
            "facet": {
              "showOtherSeries": false
            },
            "nrqlQueries": [
              {
                "accountIds": [0],
                "query": "FROM Metric SELECT latest(status)"
              }
            ],
            "platformOptions": {
              "ignoreTimeRange": false
            }
          }
        },
        {
        
          "title": "Cluster Size",
          "layout": {
            "column": 5,
            "row": 2,
            "width": 4,
            "height": 2
          },
          "linkedEntityGuids": [],
          "visualization": {
            "id": "viz.table"
          },
          "rawConfiguration": {
            "facet": {
              "showOtherSeries": false
            },
            "nrqlQueries": [
              {
                "accountIds": [0],
                "query": "SELECT \n  latest(elasticsearch.cluster.nodes) AS 'Total Nodes', \n  latest(elasticsearch.cluster.data_nodes) AS 'Data Nodes' \nFROM Metric"
              }
            ],
            "platformOptions": {
              "ignoreTimeRange": false
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "title": "Pending Tasks",
          "layout": {
            "column": 9,
            "row": 2,
            "width": 4,
            "height": 2
          },
          "linkedEntityGuids": [],
          "visualization": {
            "id": "viz.line"
          },
          "rawConfiguration": {
            "facet": {
              "showOtherSeries": false
            },
            "legend": {
              "enabled": true
            },
            "markers": {
              "displayedTypes": {
                "criticalViolations": false,
                "deployments": true,
                "relatedDeployments": true,
                "warningViolations": false
              }
            },
            "nrqlQueries": [
              {
                "accountIds": [0],
                "query": "SELECT latest(elasticsearch.cluster.pending_tasks) \nFROM Metric \nTIMESERIES"
              }
            ],
            "platformOptions": {
              "ignoreTimeRange": false
            },
            "thresholds": {
              "isLabelVisible": true
            },
            "yAxisLeft": {
              "zero": true
            },
            "yAxisRight": {
              "zero": true
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "title": "Cluster Shards",
          "layout": {
            "column": 1,
            "row": 4,
            "width": 4,
            "height": 1
          },
          "linkedEntityGuids": null,
          "visualization": {
            "id": "viz.markdown"
          },
          "rawConfiguration": {
            "text": "This is the reason behind a Yellow or Red cluster status. If you see any unassigned shards, you know exactly why the cluster is unhealthy. A high number of relocating or initializing shards indicates the cluster is rebalancing data."
          }
        },
        {
          "title": "Cluster Size",
          "layout": {
            "column": 5,
            "row": 4,
            "width": 4,
            "height": 1
          },
          "linkedEntityGuids": null,
          "visualization": {
            "id": "viz.markdown"
          },
          "rawConfiguration": {
            "text": "Monitor your data growth against capacity plans. A sudden, unexpected drop can alert you to an ingestion problem or an accidental data deletion that needs immediate investigation."
          }
        },
        {
          "title": "Cluster Shards",
          "layout": {
            "column": 9,
            "row": 4,
            "width": 4,
            "height": 1
          },
          "linkedEntityGuids": null,
          "visualization": {
            "id": "viz.markdown"
          },
          "rawConfiguration": {
            "text": "Track this trend to accurately forecast when to add more disk space, preventing storage-related outages and managing costs. A sudden increase can also help you spot and address unexpected data growth from a new application or misconfigured log source."
          }
        },
        {
          "title": "Cluster Health",
          "layout": {
            "column": 1,
            "row": 5,
            "width": 4,
            "height": 2
          },
          "linkedEntityGuids": [],
          "visualization": {
            "id": "viz.table"
          },
          "rawConfiguration": {
            "facet": {
              "showOtherSeries": false
            },
            "nrqlQueries": [
              {
                "accountIds": [0],
                "query": "SELECT latest(elasticsearch.cluster.shards) \nFROM Metric \nFACET state"
              }
            ],
            "platformOptions": {
              "ignoreTimeRange": false
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "title": "Pending Tasks",
          "layout": {
            "column": 5,
            "row": 5,
            "width": 4,
            "height": 2
          },
          "linkedEntityGuids": [],
          "visualization": {
            "id": "viz.stacked-bar"
          },
          "rawConfiguration": {
            "facet": {
              "showOtherSeries": false
            },
            "legend": {
              "enabled": true
            },
            "markers": {
              "displayedTypes": {
                "criticalViolations": false,
                "deployments": true,
                "relatedDeployments": true,
                "warningViolations": false
              }
            },
            "nrqlQueries": [
              {
                "accountIds": [0],
                "query": "SELECT latest(elasticsearch.index.documents) AS 'Total Documents in cluster'\nFROM Metric \nWHERE elasticsearch.index.name = '_all' AND aggregation = 'primary_shards' TIMESERIES "
              }
            ],
            "platformOptions": {
              "ignoreTimeRange": false
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "title": "Cluster Size",
          "layout": {
            "column": 9,
            "row": 5,
            "width": 4,
            "height": 2
          },
          "linkedEntityGuids": [],
          "visualization": {
            "id": "viz.billboard"
          },
          "rawConfiguration": {
            "facet": {
              "showOtherSeries": false
            },
            "nrqlQueries": [
              {
                "accountIds": [0],
                "query": "SELECT sum(elasticsearch.node.shards.size) / 1073741824 as 'Total Size on Disk (GB)' FROM Metric"
              }
            ],
            "platformOptions": {
              "ignoreTimeRange": false
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "title": "Pending Tasks",
          "layout": {
            "column": 1,
            "row": 7,
            "width": 4,
            "height": 1
          },
          "linkedEntityGuids": null,
          "visualization": {
            "id": "viz.markdown"
          },
          "rawConfiguration": {
            "text": "This widget shows the workload of your cluster in terms of its two primary functions: writing (indexing) and reading (searching) data.\nMonitor the rate of operations to understand your cluster's traffic patterns. A sudden drop in indexing rate could signal an issue with your data pipeline, while a spike in search rate could explain an increase in CPU or JVM load."
          }
        },
        {
          "title": "Cluster Memory",
          "layout": {
            "column": 5,
            "row": 7,
            "width": 4,
            "height": 1
          },
          "linkedEntityGuids": null,
          "visualization": {
            "id": "viz.markdown"
          },
          "rawConfiguration": {
            "text": "This shows the overall memory pressure on your cluster.If the average is consistently creeping up, it's an early warning to check individual nodes for memory hotspots or to plan for a memory upgrade across the cluster."
          }
        },
        {
          "title": "Cluster Throughput",
          "layout": {
            "column": 1,
            "row": 8,
            "width": 4,
            "height": 3
          },
          "linkedEntityGuids": null,
          "visualization": {
            "id": "viz.line"
          },
          "rawConfiguration": {
            "nrqlQueries": [
              {
                "accountIds": [0],
                "query": "SELECT rate(sum(elasticsearch.node.operations.completed), 1 second) FROM Metric FACET operation  TIMESERIES "
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "title": "Cluster CPU Usage",
          "layout": {
            "column": 5,
            "row": 8,
            "width": 4,
            "height": 3
          },
          "linkedEntityGuids": null,
          "visualization": {
            "id": "viz.line"
          },
          "rawConfiguration": {
            "nrqlQueries": [
              {
                "accountIds": [0],
                "query": "SELECT average((jvm.memory.heap.used / jvm.memory.heap.max) * 100) AS 'Avg Heap Used %' FROM Metric"
              }
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
